{"abstract": "The wireless carrier is under pressure from privacy groups after it introduced tracking code that can\u2019t be deleted by consumers.", "web_url": "https://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/01/30/verizon-wireless-to-allow-complete-opt-out-of-mobile-supercookies/", "snippet": "The wireless carrier is under pressure from privacy groups after it introduced tracking code that can\u2019t be deleted by consumers.", "lead_paragraph": "Verizon Wireless, which has been under fire by privacy advocates since late last year, has decided to make a major revision to its mobile ad-targeting program. Users who do not want to be tracked with an identifier that Verizon uses for ad-targeting purposes will soon be able to completely opt out, the company said on Friday.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/30/technology/30bits-verizon/30bits-verizon-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 407, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/01/30/technology/30bits-verizon/30bits-verizon-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 407}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/30/technology/30bits-verizon/30bits-verizon-jumbo.jpg", "height": 694, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/30/technology/30bits-verizon/30bits-verizon-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1389, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/30/technology/30bits-verizon/30bits-verizon-thumbStandard.jpg", "height": 75, "width": 75, "subType": "thumbnail", "crop_name": "thumbStandard", "legacy": {"thumbnail